<!-- ===============================================
     SECTION 2: WHY THIS AREA
================================================ -->
<section style="background:var(--color-base, #f2efe9); padding:80px 24px;">
  <div style="max-width:800px; margin:0 auto;">
    <p style="font-family:var(--font-sans); font-size:0.75rem; font-weight:700; letter-spacing:0.15em; text-transform:uppercase; color:#c4912a; margin-bottom:1rem;">Local Expertise</p>
    <h2 style="font-family:var(--font-serif); font-size:clamp(1.8rem, 3.5vw, 2.8rem); font-weight:300; line-height:1.2; color:#1c1917; margin-bottom:1.75rem;">The established southern Brisbane suburb that families target for its Mansfield State High School catchment, its well-maintained residential streets, and a community character built over decades of owner-occupier stability.</h2>
    <p style="font-family:var(--font-sans); font-size:1rem; font-weight:300; line-height:1.8; color:#4a4540; margin-bottom:1.25rem;">
      Mansfield sits approximately fourteen kilometres south of the Brisbane CBD, positioned between Wishart, Carindale, and Mount Gravatt East in Brisbane's southern residential corridor. The suburb is defined, more than by any other single factor, by the Mansfield State High School catchment. Mansfield High is one of the most consistently sought-after school catchments in the Brisbane south, and the demand that families generate to locate within it provides Mansfield with a floor of buyer competition that distinguishes it from surrounding suburbs. Sellers who understand the role that catchment access plays in their buyer's decision-making are better positioned to market their property in a way that speaks directly to that motivation.
    </p>
<!-- APPRAISAL FORM -->
