<!-- END APPRAISAL FORM -->
    <p style="font-family:var(--font-sans); font-size:1rem; font-weight:300; line-height:1.8; color:#4a4540; margin-bottom:1.25rem;">
      Beyond the school catchment, Mansfield offers a genuine residential quality that reflects decades of stable owner-occupier investment. The suburb's streets are well-maintained, its parks and green spaces are a consistent feature of the environment, and the surrounding suburb cluster, Wishart to the west, Carindale to the north-east, Mount Gravatt East to the north, gives residents access to a comprehensive range of retail, dining, and community amenity without the density of inner-city addresses. Pacific Motorway and Logan Motorway access makes the suburb practical for professionals commuting across Brisbane or to the Gold Coast.
    </p>
    <p style="font-family:var(--font-sans); font-size:1rem; font-weight:300; line-height:1.8; color:#4a4540; margin-bottom:1.25rem;">
      The housing stock in Mansfield is predominantly detached family homes reflecting the suburb's post-war and mid-century development history, with a supply of renovated and updated homes as long-term owners have improved their properties over time. Properties that present well, sit in the right catchment position, and offer the functional layout and outdoor space that families prioritise consistently attract focused competition in this market.
    </p>
    <div style="display:flex; gap:1.5rem; flex-wrap:wrap;">
      <div style="flex:1; min-width:200px; background:#fff; padding:1.75rem; border-left:3px solid #c4912a;">
        <p style="font-family:var(--font-serif); font-size:1.1rem; font-weight:400; color:#1c1917; margin-bottom:0.4rem;">Mansfield Specialist</p>
        <p style="font-family:var(--font-sans); font-size:0.85rem; font-weight:300; color:#6b6560;">Southern Brisbane Corridor</p>
